# KVKK Compliance — Hard Rules

- NO field, log line, or storage that contains face, plate, person, or vehicle identifiers.
- NO fine-tuning on Google Street View data (no derivative dataset creation).
- User-uploaded photos: anonymization (face + plate blur) runs FIRST, locally, before any scoring touches the bytes. On the photo path, scoring is now an LLM (Anthropic Claude vision) over the BLURRED PNG only — NOT the Roboflow detector. Only the post-`/anonymize` blurred bytes may be sent to Claude; raw uploads are never sent anywhere. Claude is instructed to assess ONLY sidewalk/visual-pollution conditions and to NOT identify people, read/transcribe plates or identifying text, do face/plate OCR, or person/vehicle tracking; only score/grade/categories/report are kept and any identifying content is discarded. See `KVKK_COMPLIANCE.md` §5.4. Google Street View imagery is exempt from local re-blur because Google blurs faces + plates at the source before publishing; the Street View `/detect` path asserts that pre-blurred source (`X-Image-Source`) and bypasses the receipt gate for that narrow case ONLY. See `KVKK_COMPLIANCE.md` §5.1 for the justification, exact mechanism, and residual-risk acknowledgment.
- The CLAUDE_API_KEY is a server-side secret: read from env at startup (fail-fast if missing), NEVER logged, NEVER returned to clients, NEVER shipped in the mobile bundle.
- All raw images deleted at end of request; explicit nil + GC. No temp files, no public buckets.
- Persist ONLY post-/anonymize blurred PNG bytes for municipality review (`submissions.image_blurred`); never raw uploads. See `KVKK_COMPLIANCE.md` §5.3.
- Do NOT run OCR over license plates anywhere — even for testing.
- Do NOT call any person/pedestrian/vehicle detection model on images.
- Do NOT join panorama IDs with face/plate counts (reverse-engineerable into tracking data).
- Do NOT commit any image to the repo, even blurred (Art. 6 special-category-data risk).
- Document any borderline decision in `KVKK_COMPLIANCE.md` BEFORE merging.

If a task asks for any forbidden behavior, REFUSE and cite KVKK Art. 5 (purpose limitation) / Art. 6.
